.TH "ubifs_jnl_change_xattr" 9 "ubifs_jnl_change_xattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_jnl_change_xattr \- change an extended attribute.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_jnl_change_xattr
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "const struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "const struct inode *host "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "inode" 12
extended attribute inode
.IP "host" 12
host inode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function writes the updated version of an extended attribute inode and
the host inode to the journal (to the base head). The host inode is written
after the extended attribute inode in order to guarantee that the extended
attribute will be flushed when the inode is synchronized by '\fBfsync\fP' and
consequently, the write-buffer is synchronized. This function returns zero
in case of success and a negative error code in case of failure.
